SIMPLE: stepping-stone
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Stepping-stone
<hw>Step"ping-stone`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
stone to raise the feet above the surface of water or mud in
walking.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Fig.: A means of progress or advancement.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>These obstacles his genius had turned into
<qex>stepping-stones</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Macaulay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>That men may rise on <qex>stepping-stones</qex>⟦br⟧
Of their dead selves to higher things.</q>
<rj><qau>Tennyson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stepsister</ent>⟦br⟧
